  <refnamediv>
    <refname>manderlbot</refname>
    <refpurpose>
      An erlang IRC bot
    </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>manderlbot</command>
      <arg><option>-c</option> configuration file</arg>
      <arg><option>-f</option> log file</arg>
      <arg><option>-l</option> log level</arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>description</title>
    <para>
      <command>manderlbot</command> is an irc bot aimed at saying
    idioties or doing some little searches on the internet. It is not
    an eggdrop bot.
    </para>

    <para>
      The default config file can be found in
      <filename>/etc/manderlbot/config.xml</filename>. It can includes
      some fortune files, wich you can provide in the same directory.
      </para>

  <refsect1>
    <title>options</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-c</option></term>
        <listitem>
          <para>specifies the configuration file to use.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term><option>-f</option></term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>specifies the log file to use.</para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
	<term><option>-l</option></term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>specifies the log_level from wich you want manderlbot to log in the log_file. You can specify one of the following entries :
	  </para>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term>
	    <option>emerg</option>
	    <option>alert</option>
	    <option>crit</option>
	    <option>error</option>
	    <option>warn</option>
	    <option>notice</option>
	    <option>info</option>
	    <option>debug</option>
	  </term>
	</varlistentry>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Bugs</title>
    <para> There should be none... :)
    </para>
  </refsect1>

